NAME
  afmt - format Lua source code

SYNOPSIS
  afmt [-w | -c] [--watch] <file.lua> [...]

DESCRIPTION
  Reparses Lua source through Aurora's parser and regenerates it with consistent
  two-space indentation, spaced operators and minimal parentheses. The transform
  is meaning-preserving and idempotent.

OPTIONS
  -w        rewrite the file(s) in place (atomic write)
  -c        check only: print unformatted files, exit non-zero if any differ
  --watch   re-run on every file change until interrupted (Ctrl-Alt-C)

EXAMPLES
  afmt myprog.lua            print the formatted version
  afmt -w *.lua              reformat files in place
  afmt --watch -w main.lua   keep main.lua formatted as you edit it
